# Doc set & screenshots

The doc set is part of the deliverable, not an afterthought. The
canonical files:

- `README.md` — first-contact pitch, quickstart, hero screenshots.
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — developer deep dive: modules, data flow,
  mermaid diagrams, cache-key recipe, ePub round-trip invariants.
- `docs/USAGE.md` — curator-side tour of every screen, screenshot per
  feature.
- `docs/screenshots/` — PNGs captured by `tools/snap.mjs` in `?mock=1`
  mode. `docs/screenshots/README.md` is the capture-list contract;
  filenames are stable.

## When to refresh

- **New screen / route.** Add a section to `docs/USAGE.md`, register
  the capture in `tools/snap.mjs`, add the entry to the capture list in
  `docs/screenshots/README.md`, and re-run `node tools/snap.mjs`
  against a `npm run dev` server. If routing shifts, edit the route
  diagram in `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`.
- **Existing screen materially changed** (layout, status copy, primary
  CTA). Re-run the snap script for the affected filename(s); review
  alt-text in README / USAGE.
- **New module** under `src/core/`, `src/db/`, `src/glossary/`,
  `src/llm/`, `src/lore/`, or `src/formats/` — add it to the code-
  layout tree and the relevant subsystem section in
  `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`.
- **New Dexie table, status enum, cache-key input, prompt input, or
  bundle artifact** — update the matching section in
  `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` (and the bundle layout in `README.md`, if the
  artifact is curator-visible).
- **README front-page change** (value prop, hero shot, quickstart) —
  keep the same claims true in `docs/USAGE.md` and the README must
  still match the live UI.

## Screenshot rules

- Capture only via `tools/snap.mjs` in `?mock=1` mode. Never commit
  screenshots taken against a real LLM endpoint — keys and costs leak.
- The script resets every Dexie DB at start; if a new screen needs a
  different seed, extend the script rather than capturing by hand.
- Filenames are the contract — keep them stable across runs.
